Creating business continuity (BC) and disaster recovery (DR) plans is an essential part of any organization's risk management strategy. Here are some general steps to follow when developing these plans:
- Assess Risks
- Establish a Recovery Time Objective (RTO) and Recovery Point Objective (RPO)
- Develop Response Plans: 
- Test and Validate
- Update and Maintain: 

## BC/DR Plans:
Business continuity (BC) and disaster recovery (DR) plans are critical components of an organization's risk management strategy, and their success depends on a variety of factors. Factors to be considered when developing and implementing BC/DR plans:
- Business Impact Analysis (BIA)
- Risk Assessment
- Resource allocation
- Communication
- Testing and Validation
- Continuous Improvement

### IRM Emerging trends:
As technology continues to evolve and become more integrated into business operations, new risks emerge, and it is important for organizations to stay up to date on emerging trends in IRM. The following are some IRM emerging trends
- IA and machine learning
- Cloud computing
- Supply Chain Risk Management
- Data Privacy
